cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with consensus on a network and proposes a preconditioner to adapt the weights of the graph. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper investigates the gain of a second-order filtering and proposes a cost function to achieve fastest convergence. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is another possible category as consensus is a fundamental problem in multiagent systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a polynomial filter to accelerate convergence towards consensus. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper highlights a possible loss of robustness of the polynomial filter.
